[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"1. **Primary Request and Intent**: The user wants to automate processing of 1000+ online courses from their external hard drive to create organized SOPs and eBooks. Initially focused on DIY setup using Google Drive/NotebookLM integration, then explored TigerData cloud storage, evolved to comprehensive automation solutions, and finally shifted to hiring a professional automation expert for remote setup. Core requirements throughout: cost-effective, fast processing (3-5 courses/hour), 95% accuracy, incremental processing for new content, and completely hands-off operation. 2. **Latest User Message Intent**: User specifically requests research on actual freelancer profiles who meet exact technical criteria for their automation project. They want: - Specific people on Fiverr/Upwork with verified N8N + OpenAI Whisper + cloud deployment expertise - Not just general automation experts, but those who can handle this hybrid setup - Ability to hire someone for 2 hours of remote setup via Zoom - Complete project SOP with visual diagrams to explain the job requirements - Detailed table of experts who have this exact technical stack experience - Focus on finding real, vetted professionals rather than general search strategies 3. **Key Concepts and Information**: - **Storage Solution**: Wasabi Hot Storage at $49/month for 10TB vs Google Drive at $200/month - **Processing Speed**: 5 courses/hour for complete SOP+eBook generation (95% accuracy) vs 20/hour for transcription only - **Technical Stack**: N8N workflows + OpenAI Whisper + Cloud deployment (Railway/Hetzner) + Google Sheets integration - **Cost Structure**: $95-149/month total for complete automation vs $400+ for enterprise solutions - **Quality vs Speed Trade-off**: Balanced mode (5/hour, 95% accuracy) recommended over speed mode (20/hour, 60% accuracy) - **Incremental Processing**: System can monitor external drive for new folders and process automatically - **Error Prevention**: Multiple failsafes, auto-healing, and self-monitoring required 4. **Generated Files and Artifacts**: - **Course Automation Flowchart** - Visual diagram - Purpose: Show complete workflow from external drive to final outputs - Current state: Generated via image generation tool - Status: Completed for hiring documentation - **Foolproof Setup Workflow Diagram** - Visual diagram - Purpose: Illustrate zero-error setup process with safety barriers - Current state: Generated showing bulletproof automation setup - Status: Completed for project documentation 5. **Problem Solving**: - **Answered**: Storage impact of linking vs uploading → Linking doesn't count against quota but files must remain accessible - **Answered**: TigerData suitability → Not appropriate for file processing, database-focused only - **Answered**: Processing speed clarification → 5/hour realistic for quality output, 20/hour only for raw transcription - **Retrieved**: Comprehensive pricing comparison across cloud storage providers - **Completed**: Detailed technical architecture for automation system - **Completed**: Step-by-step setup guides and troubleshooting prevention 6. **Pending Tasks**: - **Research specific freelancer profiles**: Need actual names/profiles of experts meeting technical criteria - **Create hiring SOP document**: Detailed project specification for freelancer posting - **Validate expert credentials**: Check portfolios and experience with required tech stack - **Develop screening questions**: Technical validation questions for expert vetting 7. **Current Work**: I was actively researching specific automation expert profiles on Upwork, Fiverr, and other platforms to find individuals with the exact technical skills required (N8N + OpenAI Whisper + cloud deployment + bulk processing experience). Found several Upwork profiles including Sheby M., Muhammad Hasnat A., Simeon O., and others, but was in the process of analyzing their specific qualifications against the user's requirements. Rec